org.apache.drill.exec.physical.resultSet.project

Enum ProjectionType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ProjectionType>
      • org.apache.drill.exec.physical.resultSet.project.ProjectionType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ProjectionType>

    public enum ProjectionType
extends Enum<ProjectionType>
    Specifies the type of projection obtained by parsing the projection list. The type is returned from a query of the form "how is this column projected, if at all?"

    The projection type allows the scan framework to catch inconsistencies, such as projecting an array as a map, and so on.

        public boolean isMaybeScalar()
        We can't tell, just from the project list, if a column must be scalar. A column of the form "a" could be a scalar, but that form is also consistent with maps and arrays.

      • typeFor

        public static ProjectionType typeFor(TypeProtos.MajorType majorType)

      • isCompatible

        public boolean isCompatible(ProjectionType readType)
        Reports if this type (representing an item in a projection list) is compatible with the projection type representing an actual column produced by an operator. The check is not symmetric.

        For example, a column of type map array is compatible with a projection of type map "m.a" (project all a members of the map array), but a projection type of map array "m[1].a" is not compatible with a (non-array) map column.

        Parameters:
        readType - projection type, from #typeFor(MajorType), for an actual column
        Returns:
        true if this projection type is compatible with the column's projection type
